<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.275860>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Position of penis. A, Planopilumnus spongiosus (Nobili, 1905), male (25.6 × 19.0 mm) (ZRC 2009.349), denuded; B, Vellumnus labyrinthicus (Miers, 1884), male (13.5 × 10.8 mm) (ZRC 1999.397), denuded. Abbreviations: cn = condyle of coxa; cx 5 = coxa of fifth ambulatory leg; G 1 = first male pleopod; p = penis; s 5 – s 8 = thoracic sternites 5 to 8, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/275860/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

